<item>
            <title>[PIG-1190] Handling of quoted strings in pig-latin/grunt commands</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PIG-1190</link>
                <project id="12310730" key="PIG">Pig</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;There is some inconsistency in the way quoted strings are used/handled in pig-latin .&lt;br/&gt;
In load/store and define-ship commands, files are specified in quoted strings , and the file name is the content within the quotes.  But in case of register, set, and file system commands , if string is specified in quotes, the quotes are also included as part of the string. This is not only inconsistent , it is also unintuitive. &lt;br/&gt;
This is also inconsistent with the way hdfs commandline (or bash shell) interpret file names.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;For example, currently with the command - &lt;br/&gt;
set job.name &apos;job123&apos;&lt;br/&gt;
The job name set set to &apos;job123&apos; (including the quotes) not job123 .&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This needs to be fixed, and above command should be considered equivalent to - set job.name job123. &lt;/p&gt;</description>
